20:
I think he's from that Shibuya place.
Evidently he's part of Alk and
Nimbus' group.
22:
Them again?! How many monsters
are they friends with anyway?!
29:
Here's the gems you asked for. This
enough?
33:
Wowzers! These are some
high-quality elemental gems!
They're more than enough for the
quest you accepted, but the
academy might be more
interested...
36:
Then give 'em to the higher bidder. I
can always get more.
41:
C-could you wait here for just a
moment? Sharon!
46: It really IS you! I'm Yuto, Kenji's friend—
49:
...I recognize you. All right, let's take
this outside and get it over with.
52:
I-I'm not trying to fight you! I'm on
your side!
57:
Yeah... Aegis split up, b-but I knew
you'd return, so I've been waiting this
whole time!
59:
You've gotta come back to us,
Tohru! I bet you can blow away all
those traitors in an instant! Just like
when you saved me—
62:
S-sorry for the wait. We ended up
deciding to just give you the market
value for the gems.
70:
Yuto, right? Just how long are you
gonna stay in dreamland?
73:
Listen to me—Aegis was nothing
more than a tool I used to get what I
wanted. It's of no use to me now.
76:
So leave me out of this... I've got
nothing more to give.
81:
You swore on that grave, didn't
you?! You said you'd get revenge!
84:
Me? Avenge that scumbag? Ha...
You kids will believe anything.
87: Guess I forgot all the lies I told.
101:
Do you, uh... not get along with your
family or something?
104:
Happened to overhear your talk
back at the Guild. You're super
protective of your sister, so I guess
I'm a bit confused.
106:
I remember hearing about Kazuya
Sengaku too. Real charismatic,
evidently...
109:
Ah, not that you have to answer me
or anything... I just... I mean, Aegis
and Kazuya were part of your family,
weren't they?
112:
I've never met a bigger scumbag
than my brother.
115:
Money, cash, dough. That's all he
cared about, and he didn't care
where it came from. He even took
the money set aside for Chika.
117:
Aside from terrorizing his brother
and smacking his sister, all he knew
was how to TAKE. It's no wonder he
got himself killed.
119:
It wasn't his charisma that attracted
people to Aegis. Rats like him just
tend to form packs.
123: But... you took over for him.
126:
Yeah, to get Chika out of that
hellhole. That's it.
128:
Which makes me the sleaziest rat of
them all... Your suspicions about me
are right. I haven't changed.
132: Is that why you're trying to leave?
135:
Ha... You and I are more alike than I
thought.
142:
Both of us give up before we've even
started, but we still expect so much
of others.
149:
Like how you're about to abandon
your sister in the hope that she'll
stay "pure" or whatever.
152:
I bet you can't STAND seeing people
who never give up...
160:
Like I said, you and I are pretty
similar.
162:
At least I'm trying to change though.
Sulking isn't gonna do me any good
when everyone else is moving
forward.
170:
...Whatever. Don't use me as the test
audience for your little speech.
177:
Man, why's his face gotta be so
INTENSE?!
181:
Seriously... I thought my knees were
gonna give out...
199:
Toss me that money. I'd rather hand
it over myself.
207:
By the way, if you want to put on the
tough guy act, you gotta commit.
209:
Dropping it the minute you're alone
just makes you look like an idiot.
